text.section:
To accomplish the purposes of KRS 146.650 to 146.666, the board is authorized to:
Acquire and hold property by deed, gift, devise, bequest, lease, exchange, purchase, or transfer;
Plan for, develop, construct, and maintain buildings;
Enter into agreements with state, federal, or local agencies;
Employ and contract with individuals, corporations, or other business entities to accomplish the purposes of KRS 146.650 to 146.666;
Accept and administer appropriations, gifts, grants, devises, and bequests of money, securities, or other items of value; and
Carry out any other functions necessary to accomplish the purposes of KRS 146.650 to 146.666.
